configuration.name: Base Url
configuration.description: The base url for your Good Data app (e.g. 'myapp.com')

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Active User ID
configuration.description: The ID of the authenticated user

configuration.name: GoodData Temporary Token
configuration.description: A short-lived TT (Temporary Token), which you obtain when you call gdc/account/token using your SST. You use the TT to make API calls to the GoodData platform

configuration.name: GoodData Super Secure Token
configuration.description: A long-lived SST (SuperSecure Token), which you obtain when you log in to the GoodData platform using your GoodData credentials or SSO credentials

configuration.name: Expires In
configuration.description: Amount of time until token expires

configuration.name: Product Name
configuration.description: Product name; can include your company name; must not contain spaces or slashes ( / )

configuration.name: Product Version
configuration.description: Product version; must not contain spaces or slashes ( / )

configuration.name: Active User ID
configuration.description: The ID of the authenticated user

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Authentication Time
configuration.description: The time of the last successful authentication
